                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d436">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.60M/21: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-08-20T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 20, 1940—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>464. Department’s 437, August 13, 6 p.m. Unless Embassy receives reply from
                    Foreign Office by August 21, Department will be forced to interpret Soviet
                    silence as rejection of its suggestions. You may in your discretion so inform
                    appropriate authorities, pointing out that shortness of time renders complete
                    liquidation by end of this week physically impossible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
